   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_BibNatdeFrance_14102_1819_05_18_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1819-05-18"/>May 10<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1819. <note>1</note>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#RecaJ1">Madame Recamier</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>You have done me the<lb/>
               favor to show so much <choice>
                  <orig>atten-<lb/>
               -tion</orig>
                  <reg>attention</reg>
               </choice> to the English friends<lb/>
               - whom I have presumed to<lb/>
               present to you, that I feel<lb/>
               the hope you will receive<lb/>
               with your most <choice>
                  <orig>encourag-<lb/>
               ing</orig>
                  <reg>encouraging</reg>
               </choice> smile and graceful<lb/>
               kindness those whom I<lb/>
               now present to you.<lb/>
               My <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeC1">brother</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeH3">his wife</persName>
               <lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeC1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.</persName> and <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeH3">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>.. Sneyd Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_BibNatdeFrance_14102_1819_05_18_page02.jpg"/>
               - My <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeC1">brother</persName> is the author<lb/>
               of those <title ref="./Workography.xml#Memoi5">memoirs of the<lb/>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeA1">Abbé Edgeworth</persName>
               </title> which<lb/>
               have been I believe <del>
                  <unclear>much</unclear>
               </del>
               <lb/>
               read with interest<lb/>
               in the French translation<lb/>
               - <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeC1">He</persName> is still fonder of good<lb/>
               society than of books,<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeH3">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Edgeworth</persName> joins him<lb/>
               in this taste, and I <choice>
                  <orig>can-<lb/>
                  not</orig>
                  <reg>cannot</reg>
               </choice> do them therefore a<lb/>
               greater favor than by<lb/>
               presenting them to<lb/>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_BibNatdeFrance_14102_1819_05_18_page03.jpg"/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#RecaJ1">Madame Recamier</persName>
            </p>
            <lb/>
            <p>Will you have the <choice>
                  <orig>good<lb/>
                  -ness</orig>
                  <reg>goodness</reg>
               </choice> to make them known<lb/>
                  to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#JordC1"> M Camille <choice>
                     <orig>Jordain</orig>
                     <reg>Jordan</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName> if he<lb/>
                  be in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Paris_FR">Paris</placeName> and to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#GeraJ1"> M</persName> &amp;<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#GeraA1">Madame <choice>
                     <orig>Degerando</orig>
                     <reg>de Gerando</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName> to<lb/>
               whom I beg to be most<lb/>
               kindly remembered.</p>
            <lb/>
            <p>Your bracelet my<lb/>
               dear Madam may <choice>
                  <orig>per-<lb/>
                  haps</orig>
                  <reg>perhaps</reg>
               </choice> sometime return<lb/>
                  to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Paris_FR">Paris</placeName> &amp; be seen by you<lb/>
               I hope on the arm of one<lb/>
               of my young sisters<lb/>
               <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_BibNatdeFrance_14102_1819_05_18_page04.jpg"/>
               whom I promise myself<lb/>
               the pleasure of presenting<lb/>
               to you.<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               Mean time accept<lb/>
               my affectionate respect.<lb/>
               and believe me<lb/>
               My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#RecaJ1">Madame Recamier</persName>
               <lb/>
               with sentiments of<lb/>
               esteem &amp; admiration<lb/>
               Yours sincerely<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
         </div>
      </body>
